item.title: New Style, Don't Know If I Like It
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

The text style doesn’t fit along with the background render. I believe that’s what people are attempting to say here.
And the screws you added to the background that are half-faded don’t really go along with it either. They almost look like they were just kind of tossed in there for extra detail.
You have lots of unused space in the image, and you concentrated most of the work into the center of it.
My point being you could make the image look like this and it’d have the same effect as your original.
